<section class="section white" id="system"><p class="section-kicker">Candidate operating model</p><h2>Four books must agree before opening night.</h2><p class="section-lede">This is not a stage-gate for bureaucracy. It is a compact operating contract that makes ownership and production conditions explicit before a model touches a consequential workflow.</p><div class="books"><article class="book" data-num="01"><h3>Scene</h3><p>Define the moment worth changing.</p><ul><li>Guest or business outcome</li><li>Named operating owner</li><li>Baseline and value hypothesis</li><li>Workflow and adoption burden</li></ul><span class="book-call">What gets better?</span></article><article class="book" data-num="02"><h3>Cue</h3><p>Define what the model may do and what humans retain.</p><ul><li>Data quality, lineage and privacy</li><li>Model task and limits</li><li>Human authority and override</li><li>Escalation and decision records</li></ul><span class="book-call">Who decides?</span></article><article class="book" data-num="03"><h3>Run</h3><p>Engineer for live conditions, not a demo.</p><ul><li>SIT, E2E, regression and performance</li><li>MLOps, latency, drift and observability</li><li>Security, rollback and recovery</li><li>Vendor/API resilience</li></ul><span class="book-call">Can it hold the scene?</span></article><article class="book" data-num="04"><h3>Review</h3><p>Use operating evidence to scale, revise, hold or retire.</p><ul><li>Adoption and retained use</li><li>ROI and service outcomes</li><li>Trust, incidents and control coverage</li><li>Learning and reusable assets</li></ul><span class="book-call">What did the run prove?</span></article></div><div class="decision-band"><div><p class="section-kicker">Decision architecture</p><h3>Make release, hold, rollback, reuse and retirement easier decisions - not heroic judgments.</h3></div><div class="decision-list"><span>Release with owner</span><span>Hold for evidence</span><span>Rollback safely</span><span>Retire deliberately</span><span>Reuse a pattern</span><span>Escalate an exception</span></div></div></section>
<section class="section dark"><p class="section-kicker">Executive performance report</p><h2>Measure the run, not the rhetoric.</h2><p class="section-lede">The portfolio should report value and technical health together. Metrics below are categories for discovery, not claims about Universal's current measures.</p><div class="scorecard"><article class="score"><b>Guest</b><p>Friction removed, relevance, response speed, satisfaction and recovery quality.</p></article><article class="score"><b>Flow</b><p>Cycle time, exception closure, service delivery, downtime and rework.</p></article><article class="score"><b>Economics</b><p>Realized benefit, cost-to-serve, platform reuse and vendor leverage.</p></article><article class="score"><b>Run state</b><p>Latency, drift, incident rate, deployment lead time and rollback time.</p></article><article class="score"><b>Trust</b><p>Control coverage, privacy exceptions, traceability and human override.</p></article><article class="score"><b>Adoption</b><p>Retained use, standard-work adherence, champion coverage and learning speed.</p></article></div></section>
<section class="section light" id="evidence"><p class="section-kicker">Why the evidence transfers</p><h2>An operator-technologist built around consequential systems.</h2><p class="section-lede">The fit is not a claim to be a career ML research scientist. It is a case for leading the technical operating system around AI: priorities, architecture boundaries, specialist teams, production readiness, adoption, accountability and measurable outcomes.</p><div class="evidence-map"><article class="evidence-row"><span class="years">2025-Present</span><h3>Vape-Jet - AI-first operating transformation</h3><p>Connecting production, quality, customer, engineering, ERP, CRM, telemetry and AI-assisted workflows in a software-enabled robotics environment.</p></article><article class="evidence-row"><span class="years">2017-Present</span><h3>DudeWorth - AI and automation advisory</h3><p>Designing AI-readiness, opportunity, agentic workflow, retrieval, human-judgment, evaluation and governance patterns.</p></article><article class="evidence-row"><span class="years">2014-2018</span><h3>Amazon - 24/7 launch and operating mechanisms</h3><p>Leading customer-backward execution for Amazon Prime Pittsburgh, with labor planning, throughput visibility, standard work and escalation.</p></article><article class="evidence-row"><span class="years">2000-2013</span><h3>Compunetics - high-reliability technology delivery</h3><p>Leading engineering, manufacturing, quality, customer delivery and complex programs where process control and technical translation mattered.</p></article><article class="evidence-row"><span class="years">2018-2022</span><h3>ZeusVu - regulated autonomy and computer vision concepts</h3><p>Operating drones with a 100% safety record and developing TensorFlow-based concepts for aerial inventory and field intelligence.</p></article></div></section>
